\begin_layout Standard
On page 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand pageref
reference "par:multiplication-as-linear-comb-of-rows"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 it was discovered that the product of a matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 left multiplied by an elementary matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

 could be calculated one row at a time by noting that each row of 
\begin_inset Formula $EA$
\end_inset

 is the linear combination of the rows of 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 with coefficients from the corresponding row of 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

.
 In symbols, row 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $EA$
\end_inset

 can be computed as 
\begin_inset Formula $(EA)_{r,:}=E_{r,1}A_{1,:}+E_{r,2}A_{2,:}+\cdots+E_{r,n}A_{n,:}$
\end_inset

.
 But this computation holds for any matrix product.
 Given any matrices 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $BA$
\end_inset

 is defined—that is, 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 has the same number of columns as 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 has rows, say 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

—row 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $BA$
\end_inset

 can be computed as
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
(BA)_{r,:}=B_{r,1}A_{1,:}+B_{r,2}A_{2,:}+\cdots+B_{r,n}A_{n,:}.\label{eq:matrix-prod-as-lin-comb-of-rows}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

This fact is helpful in understanding matrix products such as the one in
 (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:Mv-equals-b"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

).
 For example, suppose the third row of 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 is twice the first row of 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

.
 Then the third row of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{b}$
\end_inset

 must be twice the first row of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{b}$
\end_inset

.
 From (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:matrix-prod-as-lin-comb-of-rows"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

)
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{b}_{1,:} & =M_{1,1}\mathbf{v}_{1,:}+M_{1,2}\mathbf{v}_{2,:}+\cdots+M_{1,n}\mathbf{v}_{n,:}\\
\mathbf{b}_{3,:} & =M_{3,1}\mathbf{v}_{1,:}+M_{3,2}\mathbf{v}_{2,:}+\cdots+M_{3,n}\mathbf{v}_{n,:}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

but 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{3,:}=2M_{1,:}$
\end_inset

, which means 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{3,1}=2M_{1,1},\ M_{3,2}=2M_{1,2},\ldots,M_{3,n}=2M_{1,n}$
\end_inset

, so
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{b}_{3,:} & =2M_{1,1}\mathbf{v}_{1,:}+2M_{1,2}\mathbf{v}_{2,:}+\cdots+2M_{1,n}\mathbf{v}_{n,:}\\
 & =2(M_{1,1}\mathbf{v}_{1,:}+M_{1,2}\mathbf{v}_{2,:}+\cdots+M_{1,n}\mathbf{v}_{n,:})\\
 & =2\mathbf{b}_{1,:}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

As a consequence, for such a matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

, equation (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:Mv-equals-b"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

) can only have solutions if the third row of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{b}$
\end_inset

 happens to be twice the first row of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{b}$
\end_inset

.
 There are choices of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{b}$
\end_inset

 for which the equation has no solution!
\end_layout

